  "title": "feat(insights): introduce `insights` middleware (1/4)",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for submitting a pull request!\r\n  Please provide enough information so that others can review your pull request.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\nThis PR introduces `insights` middleware.\r\nIt is to automatically setup userToken across search calls and Insights api calls.\r\nOnce this middleware is added to `instantSearchInstance`, when user calls\r\n\r\n```js\r\nwindow.aa('setUserToken', userToken);\r\n// or \r\ninsightsClient('setUserToken', userToken);\r\n```\r\n\r\nthe middleware will automatically apply the userToken to the searchParameters. Then the next search call will include this userToken.\r\n\r\n**Stacked PRs**\r\n1. [introduce `insights` middleware](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/4446) ← current\r\n2. [send events from hits and refinementList](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/4456)\r\n3. [implement sendEvent in all the connectors](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/4463)\r\n4. [add tests](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/pull/4464)\r\n\r\n**examples**\r\n- basic example: https://codesandbox.io/s/instantsearchjs-jetcz?file=/src/app.js\r\n- with search-insights **umd**: https://codesandbox.io/s/instantsearchjs-zn81s?file=/src/app.js\r\n- `insightsClient: false`: https://codesandbox.io/s/instantsearchjs-1igbb?file=/src/app.js\r\n(_working example_: [esm](https://codesandbox.io/s/instantsearchjs-5qwf4?file=/src/app.js), [umd]())\r\n",
